(100,	1,	'2021-10-04 20:11:47',	'2021-10-04 17:11:47',	'On the 15th of December 2007, the Ivorian Society of Biosciences and Health Informatics (ISBHI) was created in Côte d’Ivoire, a West African country of 17 million people.\r\n\r\nThe ISBHI is a non-profit association whose main aims are to promote computer applications in health care through the organization of scientific meetings, health informatics educational efforts and to contribute to the development of information systems relevant and adaptable to the Côte d’Ivoire National Health system. The association is also known as Societe Ivoirienne de Biosciences et D’Informatique Medicale.',	'Ivorian Society of Biosciences and Health Informatics',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'ivorian-society-of-biosciences-and-health-informatics',	'',	'',	'2021-10-04 20:11:47',	'2021-10-04 17:11:47',	'',	0,	'http://localhost/dev/helina/app/?post_type=member&#038;p=100',	0,	'member',	'',	0),
