(269,	1,	'2021-10-25 03:36:37',	'2021-10-25 00:36:37',	'The next edition of the Pan-African Health informatics Association (HELINA) Conference will be hosted by the Uganda Health Informatics Association (UgHIA – <a class=\"\" href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fughia.org%2Fhome%2F&amp;data=04%7C01%7Ckristin.centers%40vumc.org%7C8da4a25f9df44f303e8508d8b0e41843%7Cef57503014244ed8b83c12c533d879ab%7C0%7C0%7C637453840986797031%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=7GIO42rYQ%2B6NAYBFb4p1A1ndgw9fjViFKOPA%2FPchh2s%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">https://ughia.org/home/</a>) in partnership with the Makerere University, School of Public Health, the Ministry of Health (MOH), Uganda and HELINA.\n\nOriginally slated for 26th – 30th of October 2020, Uganda Health Informatics Association (UgHIA) in conjunction with HELINA has changed the dates of the conference to October, 18th – 22nd, 2021. The deadline for submission of papers will be at the end of June 2021..\n\nThis is due to the public health and social measures issued by the World Health Organization (WHO) and respective Ministries of Health including that of the Uganda Government in response to the emergence of the COVID-19 pandemic, its continued persistence and unpredictability in terms of effective control and management. The measures including travel restrictions and a ban on mass gatherings have directly affected the practicality of UgHIA hosting the Conference during the earlier proposed period. The conference in October 2021 will be a blend of both virtual and in-person to accommodate those who are unable to physically attend due to the COVID-19 pandemic.\n\nThe conference will focus on <strong>“Leveraging digital health for public health emergencies within routine care in Low- and Middle-Income Countries”</strong>, providing a platform to showcase interventions in the areas of; Maturity models for digital health; Community level digital health solutions;\n\nDigital health quality: standards, interoperability, ethical, legal and regulatory issues; Open source software in healthcare delivery; eLearning and digital health training for capacity building; Innovations for remote patient monitoring and care and big data and analytics in public health emergencies with routine care.\n\nThe organizers of the conference welcome original presentations in the following categories: Full research papers; Work in progress papers; or Case study/experience presentations.\n\n<strong>For submissions, please visit <a class=\"\" href=\"https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Feasychair.org%2Fcfp%2FHELINA2021-Conference&amp;data=04%7C01%7Ckristin.centers%40vumc.org%7C8da4a25f9df44f303e8508d8b0e41843%7Cef57503014244ed8b83c12c533d879ab%7C0%7C0%7C637453840986797031%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&amp;sdata=ldt8z520%2FbpJlaDldU%2Fx41uk7UllGHt9tEDEdzhXK%2Bc%3D&amp;reserved=0\">https://easychair.org/cfp/HELINA2021-Conference</a></strong>',	'#HELINA 21 Virtual Conference',	'',	'inherit',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'89-autosave-v1',	'',	'',	'2021-10-25 03:36:37',	'2021-10-25 00:36:37',	'',	89,	'http://localhost/dev/helina/app/?p=269',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
